[1] Case updates
- Tue 25 Dec 2018. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=9958aef9a2

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 24 Dec 2018:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 583, of which 535 are confirmed and 48 are probable. In total, there were 354 deaths (306 confirmed and 48 probable) and 201 people healed.
- 122 suspect cases under investigation.
- 4 new confirmed cases, including 2 in Oicha, 1 in Butembo, and 1 in Mabalako.
- 2 new deaths of confirmed cases (all community deaths), including 1 in Oicha and 1 in Butembo.

News of the response
Christmas celebrations
-The Minister of Health, Dr. Oly Ilunga Kalenga, celebrated the Christmas party by visiting the teams of the response to Beni and Butembo this Tue 25 Dec 2018. He started his day in Butembo where he greeted and presented the wishes year-end to the teams. He then visited the Ebola Treatment Center under construction in Katwa Health Zone. Back in Beni, he surprised the coordination teams arriving at their daily meeting.

The Minister of Health warmly thanked and congratulated all these health workers from Kinshasa and around the world who agreed to spend the holidays at the end of the year away from their families to continue coping with this 10th Ebola outbreak in the DRC. Despite the difficult environment, all these people are honoring their commitment to help affected populations in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri until the end of the Ebola epidemic. For this commitment and sacrifice, the Minister of Health said that they deserve the respect and recognition of an entire nation.

Vaccination
-----------
- Continued wide-belt vaccination (or ring plus) in Otomaber (in Komanda Health Zone) and Aloya (in Mabalako Health Zone)

- Continued immunization of primary care providers in the Goma Health Zone.

- Since vaccination began on 8 Aug 2018, 52 630 people have been vaccinated, including 19 348 in Beni, 10 303 in Katwa, 5745 in Butembo, 5313 in Mabalako, 2258 in Kalunguta, 1663 in Mandima, 1177 in Komanda, 931 in Oicha, 884 in Goma, 791 in Vuhovi, 750 in Masereka, 700 in Lubero, 659 in Kyondo, 599 in Mutwanga, 434 in Bunia, 394 in Musienene, 355 in Tchomia, 167 in Nyankunde, 70 in Biena, 63 in Alimbongo, 13 in Karisimbi and 13 in Kisangani.

- The only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 19 May 2018.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteurs Kunihiko Iizuka and Mary Marshall

- Mon 24 Dec 2018. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=8511854d94

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 23 Dec 2018:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 579, of which 531 are confirmed and 48 are probable. In total, there were 352 deaths (304 confirmed and 48 probable) and 201 people healed.
- 213 suspected cases under investigation.
- 5 new confirmed cases, including 2 in Mabalako, 2 in Katwa, and 1 in Butembo.
- 5 new confirmed case deaths, including 2 in Butembo, 1 in Beni, 1 in Mabalako, and 1 in Katwa (1 community death).
- 3 new people healed out of Butembo CTE.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

